@DATABASE "ScionRexx"
@REMARK $VER: ScionRexx.guide v5.03 (1 Jul 1998)
@REMARK Amigaguide« ARexx help file for Scion Genealogist release 5

@INDEX ARexxIndex

##
## "Scion Genealogist V5 ARexx Command Help"
##

@NODE Main "Scion Genealogist V5 ARexx Command Help"
        Welcome to the Scion Genealogist V5 ARexx Command AmigaGuide«
        =============================================================

Scion Genealogist provides an ARexx interface for reading and modifying the
information contained in a database.

The default ARexx port name is SCIONGEN. If this name is not unique, or
more than one copy of Scion is running, the default ARexx port name will be
suffixed with a digit from 1 to 9. For example, SCIONGEN3. Therefore, up to
10 copies of Scion can be run, each with a unique ARexx port name.

To determine the actual ARexx port name in use, select the "Info" item in
the Project menu.

                       @{"  ARexx Command Summary " LINK CommandSummary}
                       @{"   ARexx Command Index  " LINK ARexxIndex}
                       @{"       What's New       " LINK NewCommands}

SPECIAL NOTES FOR AREXX AUTHORS:

1. With earlier versions of Scion, GETTOTALIRN and GETTOTALFGRN would
   return values equal to the last record numbers in the database if
   there had been no records deleted from the database.

   Some people used these commands to get the record number of the last
   person/family in the database, and use these values as index counters.
   This was never strictly correct, as this made no allowance for records
   that may have been deleted from the database. Don't do this any more!

   Use the new ARexx commands GETLASTIRN and GETLASTFGRN to determine the
   biggest record numbers recorded in the database.

   For example, if you have a database of 2 people with the first person
   having a record number of 12 and the second person having a record
   number of 42, GETLASTIRN will return a value of 42 (the largest record
   number), and the GETTOTALIRN command will return 2 (the number of
   people).

2. If you wish your ARexx scripts to be able to be used with earlier
   versions of Scion, make sure you don't use any of the new ARexx
   commands added for Scion V5. You can use the command GETPROGVERSION
   to determine which version of Scion is running and adapt you scripts
   behaviour appropriately.
@ENDNODE

