@REMARK Changed Command Stuff ***********************************************

##
## GETxxxDATE Numeric Format
##

@NODE GETXXXNUMERIC "GETxxxDATE Numeric Format"
                        GETxxxDATE Numeric Format
			-------------------------

With Scion V5, all the GETxxxDATE commands (eg GETBIRTHDATE) can return a
new "numeric" string format.

Using the new "numeric" format, Scion will return dates in the following
format:

       "qDD-MM-YYYYub"
where:
         q  = single character qualifier ('<', '>', '~' or nothing for
	      exact date)
        DD  = 2 digit day number (can be 00 for no day). Always 2
	      digits.
        MM  = 2 digit month number (can be 00 for no month). Always 2
	      digits.
      YYYY  = 4 digit year number. Always 4 digits.
         u  = single character uncertainty flag '?' (or nothing for certain
	      date)
         b  = 2 character "BC" (or nothing for AD dates). NOTE: This "BC"
	      is NOT localised.

   The delimiter between DD, MM and YYYY is always the single '-'
   character. The format is fixed and all numbers, qualifiers, flags, etc
   will always appear in the order according to the "template" above.

Examples -

       "24-04-1967"  - "24 April 1967" (exact date)
      ">24-04-1967"  - "After 24 April 1967"
      "<24-04-1967"  - "Before 24 April 1967"
      "~24-04-1967"  - "Circa 24 April 1967"
      "00-04-1967?"  - "April 1967?" (uncertain date with no day)
       "00-00-1967"  - "1967" (no day or month)
    "~00-00-0200BC"  - "Circa 200 BC" (BC date with no day or month)

@ENDNODE

##
## PUTxxxDATE Numeric Format
##

@NODE PUTXXXNUMERIC "PUTxxxDATE Numeric Format"
                        PUTxxxDATE Numeric Format
			-------------------------

With Scion V5, all the PUTxxxDATE commands (eg PUTBIRTHDATE) can accept
dates in a new "numeric" string format.

Because of the totally unique "tokens" making up this new "numeric" date
format, it is possible for any token in the numeric string (EXCEPT the
day, month and year) to appear in any order.

However, the RECOMMENDED format is -

       "%%%qDD-MM-YYYYub"
where:
      "%%%" = internal indicator to Scion that this date is in the new
              "numeric" format. MUST be present to indicate the new format.
         q  = single character qualifier ('<', '>', '~' or nothing for
	      exact date). Precedence is '<', '>', '~'. That is, if you
	      attempt to use "~<", only the '<' will be recognised as it
	      has a higher precedence than '~'.
        DD  = day number (can be 0 for no day). Either 1 or 2 digits, but
	      MUST be present.
        MM  = month number (can be 0 for no month). Either 1 or 2 digits,
	      but MUST be present.
      YYYY  = year number. Either 1,2,3 or 4 digits, but MUST be present.
         u  = single character uncertainty flag '?' (or nothing for
	      certain date)
         b  = 2 character "BC" (or nothing for AD dates). NOTE: Do NOT
	      localise "BC" - only "BC" will be recognised.

   The delimiter between DD, MM and YYYY can be any "non-digit" character
   (except for the "qualifier" characters), but all three fields must
   always exist (but could be 0) and MUST be in DD,MM,YYYY order. Any
   "white-space" is ignored.

Examples (using recommended format) -

        "%%%24-4-1967"  - "24 April 1967" (exact date)
      "%%%>24-04-1967"  - "After 24 April 1967"
       "%%%<24-4-1967"  - "Before 24 April 1967"
      "%%%~24-04-1967"  - "Circa 24 April 1967"
        "%%%0-4-1967?"  - "April 1967?" (uncertain date with no day)
       "%%%00-4-1967?"  - "April 1967?" (uncertain date with no day)
         "%%%0/0/1967"  - "1967" (no day or month and different delimiters)
      "%%%00-00-200BC"  - "200 BC" (BC date with no day or month)

Note that you need only use sufficient digits to set any of the DD, MM or
YYYY values. This is different to the "numeric" formats returned by
GETxxxDATE commands which will ALWAYS return 2,2,4 digits for DD,MM,YY.
@ENDNODE

@REMARK ARexx Command Stuff **************************************************

##
## "GETDBNAME"
##

@NODE getdbname "GETDBNAME"
GETDBNAME command:

Obtain the name of the current database

	SYNTAX:	GETDBNAME

	result: Name of current database (could be "Unnamed").

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	GETDBNAME		/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	Say "Current database name is " RESULT

See also @{" GETDBPATH " link getdbpath}
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETDBPATH"
##

@NODE getdbpath "GETDBPATH"
GETDBPATH command:

Obtain the path to the currently loaded database, or the current location
of Scion if no database is loaded.

	SYNTAX:	GETDBPATH

	result: Path to the currently loaded database, or the current
                location of Scion if no database is loaded.

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

NOTES: (1) Returns the path in the form "Work:Data/Example" (no
           terminating '/'), or "MYDATA:Example" (where "MYDATA" is an
           existing assign).
       (2) The maximum length of the returned result is 255 characters.
           If you get a RESULT of 255 characters you can probably be
           fairly certain that the result has been truncated! If you are
           concerned about this, you should check the length of RESULT
           and behave accordingly.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	GETDBPATH		/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	Say "Current database path is " RESULT

See also @{" GETDBNAME " link getdbname}
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETTOTALIRN"
##

@NODE gettotalirn "GETTOTALIRN"
GETTOTALIRN command:

Obtain the total number of people in the database.

	SYNTAX:	GETTOTALIRN

	result: Total number of people in the database.
	        NOTE: This also includes any deleted people.

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	GETTOTALIRN		/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	Say "Number of people in database = " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETCURRENTIRN"
##

@NODE getcurrentirn "GETCURRENTIRN"
GETCURRENTIRN command:

Obtain the IRN of the currently displayed person.

	SYNTAX:	GETCURRENTIRN

	result: The IRN of the currently displayed person.
	        NOTE: This also includes any deleted people.

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	GETCURRENTIRN		/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	Say "Currently displayed person = " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETTOTALFGRN"
##

@NODE gettotalfgrn "GETTOTALFGRN"
GETTOTALFGRN command:

Obtain the total number of family groups in the database.

	SYNTAX:	GETTOTALFGRN

	result: Total number of family groups in the database.
	        NOTE: This also includes any dissolved family groups.

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	GETTOTALFGRN		/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	Say "Number of families in database = " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETFIRSTIRN"
##

@NODE getfirstirn "GETFIRSTIRN"
GETFIRSTIRN command:				(V5)

Obtain the lowest numbered person's IRN

	SYNTAX: GETFIRSTIRN

	Returns the lowest numbered person's IRN (or 0 for no people)

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyIRN = 5		/* Set MyIRN to person 5 */
	GETFIRSTIRN MyIRN	/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	if RESULT = 0 then
	do
		Say "Nobody in database"
	end
	else
		Say "First person's IRN =" RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETLASTIRN"
##

@NODE getlastirn "GETLASTIRN"
GETLASTIRN command:			(V5)

Obtain the highest numbered person's IRN

	SYNTAX: GETLASTIRN

	Returns the highest numbered person's IRN (or 0 for no people)

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyIRN = 5		/* Set MyIRN to person 5 */
	GETLASTIRN MyIRN	/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	if RESULT = 0 then
	do
		Say "Nobody in database"
	end
	else
		Say "Last person's IRN =" RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETNEXTIRN"
##

@NODE getnextirn "GETNEXTIRN"
GETNEXTIRN command:			(V5)

Obtain the next person's IRN after the specified IRN

	SYNTAX: GETNEXTIRN irn

	where: 'irn' is the IRN of the person of interest in the Scion
		database

	result: The next person's IRN after the specified IRN. For example,
	        if the people are numbered 2,4,67,92, then "GETNEXTIRN 67"
		will return 92.

		If 'irn' is not specified or is 0, returns the next person's
		IRN after the currently displayed person.

		If no next person is found, returns 0.

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyIRN = 5		/* Set MyIRN to person 5 */
	GETNEXTIRN MyIRN	/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	if RESULT = 0 then
	do
		Say "Next person was not found in database"
	end
	else
		Say "Next person's IRN =" RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETPREVIRN"
##

@NODE getprevirn "GETPREVIRN"
GETPREVIRN command:			(V5)

Obtain the previous person's IRN before the specified IRN

	SYNTAX: GETPREVIRN irn

	where: 'irn' is the IRN of the person of interest in the Scion
		database

	result: the previous person's IRN before the specified IRN. For
		example, if the people are numbered 2,4,67,92, then
		"GETPREVIRN 67" will return 4.

		If 'irn' is not specified or is 0, returns the previous
		person's IRN before the currently displayed person.

		If no previous person is found, returns 0.

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyIRN = 5		/* Set MyIRN to person 5 */
	GETPREVIRN MyIRN	/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	if RESULT = 0 then
	do
		Say "Previous person was not found in database"
	end
	else
		Say "Previous person's IRN =" RESULT

@ENDNODE

