## "GETFIRSTNAME"
##

@NODE getfirstname "GETFIRSTNAME"
GETFIRSTNAME command:

Obtain the first name(s) of the specified person

	SYNTAX:	GETFIRSTNAME CurrentIRN

	where: 'CurrentIRN' is the IRN of the person
	       of interest in the Scion database

	result: The first name(s) of the specified person

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyIRN = 5		/* Set MyIRN to person 5 */
	GETFIRSTNAME MyIRN	/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	Say "Person's first name is:" RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETSEX"
##

@NODE getsex "GETSEX"
GETSEX command:

Obtain the sex (gender) of the specified person

	SYNTAX:	GETSEX CurrentIRN

	where: 'CurrentIRN' is the IRN of the person
	       of interest in the Scion database

	result: The sex (gender) of the specified person

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyIRN = 5		/* Set MyIRN to person 5 */
	GETSEX MyIRN		/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	Say "Person's gender is:" RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETBIRTHDATE"
##

@NODE getbirthdate "GETBIRTHDATE"
GETBIRTHDATE command:

Obtain the date of birth of the specified person

	SYNTAX:	GETBIRTHDATE CurrentIRN NUMERIC_FMT

	where: 'CurrentIRN' is the IRN of the person
	       of interest in the Scion database

	  (v5) If NUMERIC_FMT is present AND non-zero, then the date is
	       returned as a 'numeric' string in "DD-MM-YYYY" format (for
	       example, "29-04-1947"). Otherwise the date is returned
	       in the default "DD MMM YYYY" format (eg. "29 Apr 1947").

	       Note that, with 'numeric' format, 'DD' may be "00" (no day
	       supplied) and that 'MM' may also be "00" (no month
	       supplied).

	result: The date of birth of the specified person

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyIRN = 5		/* Set MyIRN to person 5 */
	GETBIRTHDATE MyIRN	/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	Say "Person's date of birth is:" RESULT
	GETBIRTHDATE MyIRN 1	/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	Say "Person's 'numeric' date of birth is:" RESULT

See also @{" GETxxxDATE Numeric Format " LINK GETXXXNUMERIC}.
@ENDNODE

