	  (v5) If NUMERIC_FMT is present AND non-zero, then the date is
	       returned as a 'numeric' string in "DD-MM-YYYY" format (for
	       example, "29-04-1947"). Otherwise the date is returned
	       in the default "DD MMM YYYY" format (eg. "29 Apr 1947").

	       Note that, with 'numeric' format, 'DD' may be "00" (no day
	       supplied) and that 'MM' may also be "00" (no month
	       supplied).

	result: The date of baptism of the specified person

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyIRN = 5		/* Set MyIRN to person 5 */
	GETBAPTISMDATE MyIRN	/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	Say "Person's date of baptism is:" RESULT
	GETBAPTISMDATE MyIRN 1	/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	Say "Person's 'numeric' date of baptism is:" RESULT

See also @{" GETxxxDATE Numeric Format " LINK GETXXXNUMERIC}.
@ENDNODE

