##
## "GETISDEAD"
##

@NODE getisdead "GETISDEAD"
GETISDEAD command:				(V5.08)

Ask whether the specified person is dead

	SYNTAX:	GETISDEAD CurrentIRN

	where: 'CurrentIRN' is the IRN of the person
	       of interest in the Scion database

	result: 0 (FALSE) for 'alive', 1 (TRUE) for 'dead'

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

	NOTE: Death is TRUE if either -
	      (1) the person has a death date, or
	      (2) the person has a burial date, or
	      (3) the person's death date is marked "Dead (no date)"

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyIRN = 5		/* Set MyIRN to person 5 */
	GETISDEAD MyIRN		/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	if(RESULT) then say "Person is dead"
	else say "Person is (probably) alive"
@ENDNODE

