##
## "GETENGAGEDATE"
##

@NODE getengagedate "GETENGAGEDATE"
GETENGAGEDATE command:

Obtain the date of engagement for the specified family

	SYNTAX:	GETENGAGEDATE CurrentFGRN NUMERIC_FMT

	where: 'CurrentFGRN' is the FGRN of the family
	       of interest in the Scion database

	  (v5) If NUMERIC_FMT is present AND non-zero, then the date is
	       returned as a 'numeric' string in "DD-MM-YYYY" format (for
	       example, "29-04-1947"). Otherwise the date is returned
	       in the default "DD MMM YYYY" format (eg. "29 Apr 1947").

	       Note that, with 'numeric' format, 'DD' may be "00" (no day
	       supplied) and that 'MM' may also be "00" (no month
	       supplied).

	result: The date of engagement for the specified family

	The result is returned in the ARexx variable RESULT.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyFGRN = 5		/* Set MyFGRN to family 5 */
	GETENGAGEDATE MyFGRN	/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	Say "Date of engagement is:" RESULT
	GETENGAGEDATE MyFGRN 1	/* Issue command to Scion Genealogist */
	Say "'Numeric' date of engagement is:" RESULT

See also @{" GETxxxDATE Numeric Format " LINK GETXXXNUMERIC}.
@ENDNODE

