## "PUTCELEBRANT"
##

@NODE putcelebrant "PUTCELEBRANT"
PUTCELEBRANT command:

Set the celebrant of the marriage for the specified family in the
database

	SYNTAX:	PUTCELEBRANT CurrentFGRN "Celebrant"

	where: 'CurrentFGRN' is the FGRN of the family
	       of interest in the Scion database

	       "Celebrant" is the celebrant of the marriage for the
	       specified family

	result: 0 (FALSE) for error, 1 (TRUE) for success (record updated)

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyFGRN = 5		/* Set MyFGRN to family 5 */
	PUTCELEBRANT MyFGRN "Rev. Smith"	/* Issue command */
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTWITNESS"
##

@NODE putwitness "PUTWITNESS"
PUTWITNESS command:

Set the witness of the marriage for the specified family in the database

	SYNTAX:	PUTWITNESS CurrentFGRN "Witness"

	where: 'CurrentFGRN' is the FGRN of the family
	       of interest in the Scion database

	       "Witness" is the witness of the marriage for the
	       specified family

	result: 0 (FALSE) for error, 1 (TRUE) for success (record updated)

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyFGRN = 5		/* Set MyFGRN to family 5 */
	PUTWITNESS MyFGRN "John Doe"	/* Issue command */
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTFAMCOMMENT"
##

@NODE putfamcomment "PUTFAMCOMMENT"
PUTFAMCOMMENT command:

Set the family comments for the specified family in the database

	SYNTAX:	PUTFAMCOMMENT CurrentFGRN "Comment"

	where: 'CurrentFGRN' is the FGRN of the family
	       of interest in the Scion database

	       "Comment" is the family comments for the specified family

	result: 0 (FALSE) for error, 1 (TRUE) for success (record updated)

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyFGRN = 5		/* Set MyFGRN to family 5 */
	PUTFAMCOMMENT MyFGRN "Husband absconded"	/* Issue command */
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTFAMREFS"
##

@NODE putfamrefs "PUTFAMREFS"
PUTFAMREFS command:

Set the family references for the specified family in the database

	SYNTAX:	PUTFAMREFS CurrentFGRN "References"

	where: 'CurrentFGRN' is the FGRN of the family
	       of interest in the Scion database

	       "References" is the family references for the specified
	       family

	result: 0 (FALSE) for error, 1 (TRUE) for success (record updated)

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyFGRN = 5		/* Set MyFGRN to family 5 */
	PUTFAMREFS MyFGRN "Marriage Certificate AB9876"	/* Issue command */
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTENDING"
##

@NODE putending "PUTENDING"
PUTENDING command:

Set the ending for the specified family in the database

	SYNTAX:	PUTENDING CurrentFGRN EndNum

	where: 'CurrentFGRN' is the FGRN of the family
	       of interest in the Scion database

	       'EndNum is the ending value for the specified family

	           Valid values are:
			0 = Unknown
			1 = None
			2 = Divorce
			3 = Separation
			4 = Annulment
			5 = Death

	           Values greater than 5 will have no effect.

	result: 0 (FALSE) for error, 1 (TRUE) for success (record updated)

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyFGRN = 5		/* Set MyFGRN to family 5 */
	PUTENDING MyFGRN 5	/* Issue command (ending = "death") */
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTFAMUSER1"
##

@NODE putfamuser1 "PUTFAMUSER1"
PUTFAMUSER1 command:
This command is now obsolete, and is equivalent to @{" PUTCELEBRANT " LINK putcelebrant}
Sets the celebrant of the specified family.
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTFAMUSER2"
##

@NODE putfamuser2 "PUTFAMUSER2"
PUTFAMUSER2 command:
This command is now obsolete, and is equivalent to @{" PUTFAMCOMMENT " LINK putfamcomment}
Sets the family comments of the specified family.
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTNEWPERSON"
##

@NODE putnewperson "PUTNEWPERSON"
PUTNEWPERSON command:

Create a new personal record in the database

	SYNTAX:	PUTNEWPERSON

	result: IRN of new record created. A return value of 0 signifies
	        a command failure because of no free space remaining.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	PUTNEWPERSON
	If RESULT = 0 then say "Command failed"
	else say "IRN of new record = " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTNUMPERSON"
##

@NODE putnumperson "PUTNUMPERSON"
PUTNUMPERSON command:			(V5)

Add a specified person to the database

	SYNTAX: PUTNUMPERSON irn

	where: 'irn' is the IRN of the person to add to the database

	result: On success, returns the number requested, else returns 0
		(maybe the specified person was already in the database).
		Note that asking for person 0 will also return 0, but this
		is ALSO a failure.

This command adds a specified person to the database (as opposed to
@{" PUTNEWPERSON " LINK putnewperson} which adds the next available person).


EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	newperson = 42		/* Number of person to add to database */
	PUTNUMPERSON newperson
	If RESULT ~= newperson then say "Command failed"
	else say "Person was added successfully"
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTNEWFAMILY"
##

@NODE putnewfamily "PUTNEWFAMILY"
PUTNEWFAMILY command:

Create a new family group record in the database

The person specified by the 'CurrentIRN' argument will be established
as the Principal of that new family group. If the specified person
already has existing marriages, this command will add an ADDITIONAL
family group to that person's list of marriages.

	SYNTAX:	PUTNEWFAMILY CurrentIRN

	where: 'CurrentIRN' is the IRN of the person that a new family
	       group is required for.

	result: FGRN of new record created. A return value of 0 signifies
	        a command failure because of no free space remaining.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyIRN = 5		/* Set MyIRN to person 5 */
	PUTNEWFAMILY MyIRN
	If RESULT = 0 then say "Command failed"
	else say "FGRN of new record = " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTSPOUSE"
##

@NODE putspouse "PUTSPOUSE"
PUTSPOUSE command:			(Modified return values for V5)

Add a spouse to an existing family group. Any existing spouse is replaced,
but children and other family group details remain unchanged.

If "SpouseIRN" = 0, then the existing spouse in the family group is
deleted from that group (no new spouse is added).

	SYNTAX:	PUTSPOUSE CurrentFGRN SpouseIRN

	where: 'CurrentFGRN' is the FGRN of the family group that the spouse
	       will be added to.

	       'SpouseIRN' is the IRN of the person to add to the family
	       group as the spouse.

	       If 'SpouseIRN' = 0, then the existing spouse in the family
	       group is deleted from that group (no new spouse is added).

	result: A return value of 1 signifies success. Other return values
	        are as follows:

		 0 = invalid command ("SpouseIRN" was probably omitted) or
		     specified family does not exist
		-1 = specified spouse does not exist.
		-2 = the spouse's personal record has been previously
		     deleted from the database. No longer applicable for
		     Scion Version 5.
		-3 = the selected spouse is the same person as the
		     principal of the family group.
		-4 = the selected spouse has already been married the
		     maximum number of times permitted.
		-5 = the selected spouse is already a child of the
		     family group.
		-6 = the selected spouse is a child of one of the children
		     in the family group. No longer applicable for
		     Scion Version 5.
                -7 = the selected spouse is one of their own descendants.
                     New for Scion Version 5.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyFGRN = 5		/* Set MyFGRN to family 5 */
	SpouseIRN = 12		/* Set SpouseIRN to 12 */
	PUTSPOUSE MyFGRN SpouseIRN
	if RESULT = 1 THEN Say "Success!"
	else Say "Failed: Error return value = " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTCHILD"
##

@NODE putchild "PUTCHILD"
PUTCHILD command:			(Modified return values for V5)

Add a child to an existing family group.

	SYNTAX:	PUTCHILD CurrentFGRN ChildIRN

	where: 'CurrentFGRN' is the FGRN of the family group that the child
	       will be added to.

	       'ChildIRN' is the IRN of the person to add to the family
	       group as a child.

	result: A return value of 1 signifies success. Other return values
	        are as follows:

		 0 = invalid command ("ChildIRN" was omitted) or
		     specified family does not exist.
		-1 = specified child does not exist.
		-2 = the family already has the maximum number of children
		-3 = the child's personal record has been previously
		     deleted from the database.
		-4 = the selected child already has parents defined
		-5 = the selected child is one of the parents of the
		     family group.
		-6 = the selected child is a parent of the principal
		     of the family group. No longer applicable for Scion
                     version 5.
		-7 = the selected child is a parent of the spouse
		     of the family group. No longer applicable for Scion
                     version 5.
		-8 = selected child is one of their own ancestors. New for
                     Scion Version 5.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyFGRN = 5		/* Set MyFGRN to family 5 */
	ChildIRN = 12		/* Set ChildIRN to 12 */
	PUTCHILD MyFGRN ChildIRN
	if RESULT = 1 THEN Say "Success!"
	else Say "Failed: Error return value = " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "UPDATEPERSONWIN"
##

@NODE updatepersonwin "UPDATEPERSONWIN"
UPDATEPERSONWIN command:			(V5)

Updates Personal Details Window to show details of person

	SYNTAX:	UPDATEPERSONWIN irn

	where: 'irn' is the IRN of the person to display.

	result: A return value of 1 (TRUE) signifies success. A return
	        value of 0 (FALSE) signifies failure.

This command updates the Personal Details Window to show details of person
'irn'. This is identical to @{" GETPERSONWIN " LINK getpersonwin}, except that this call does
NOT force the Personal Details Window to the front of the display as
GETPERSONWIN does.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	ShowIRN = 12		/* Set ShowIRN to 12 */
	UPDATEPERSONWIN ShowIRN	/* Display person's record */
	if RESULT = 1 THEN Say "Success!"
	else Say "Failed"
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETPERSONWIN"
##

@NODE getpersonwin "GETPERSONWIN"
GETPERSONWIN command:

Move to the specified person's data record and display it.
(Bring Personal Window to the front)

	SYNTAX:	GETPERSONWIN ShowIRN

	where: 'ShowIRN' is the IRN of the person to display.

	result: A return value of 1 (TRUE) signifies success. A return
	        value of 0 (FALSE) signifies failure.

	See also @{" UPDATEPERSONWIN " LINK updatepersonwin}

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	ShowIRN = 12		/* Set ShowIRN to 12 */
	GETPERSONWIN ShowIRN	/* Display person's record */
	if RESULT = 1 THEN Say "Success!"
	else Say "Failed"
@ENDNODE

##
## "UPDATEFAMILYWIN"
##

@NODE updatefamilywin "UPDATEFAMILYWIN"
UPDATEFAMILYWIN command:			(V5)

Updates Family Details Window to show details of family

	SYNTAX:	UPDATEFAMILYWIN fgrn

	where: 'fgrn' is the FGRN of the family to display.

	result: A return value of 1 (TRUE) signifies success. A return
	        value of 0 (FALSE) signifies failure.

This command updates Family Details Window to show details of family
'fgrn'. This is identical to @{" GETFAMILYWIN " LINK getfamilywin}, except that this call does
NOT force the Family Details Window to the front of the display as
GETFAMILYWIN does.


EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	ShowFGRN = 12		/* Set ShowFGRN to 12 */
	UPDATEFAMILYWIN ShowFGRN	/* Display family's record */
	if RESULT = 1 THEN Say "Success!"
	else Say "Failed"
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETFAMILYWIN"
##

@NODE getfamilywin "GETFAMILYWIN"
GETFAMILYWIN command:

Move to the specified family's data record and display it.
(Bring Family Window to the front)

	SYNTAX:	GETFAMILYWIN ShowFGRN

	where: 'ShowFGRN' is the FGRN of the family group to display.

               Move to the specified family's data record and display it.
	       (Bring Family Window to the front)

	result: A return value of 1 (TRUE) signifies success. A return
	        value of 0 (FALSE) signifies failure.

	See also @{" UPDATEFAMILYWIN " LINK updatefamilywin}

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	ShowFGRN = 12		/* Set ShowFgRN to 12 */
	GETFAMILYWIN ShowFGRN	/* Display family's record */
	if RESULT = 1 THEN Say "Success!"
	else Say "Failed"
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETPROGVERSION"
##

@NODE getprogversion "GETPROGVERSION"
GETPROGVERSION command:

Obtain the version number of Scion Genealogist

	SYNTAX:	GETPROGVERSION

	result: Programme version number

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	GETPROGVERSION		/* Get programme version number */
	Say "Programme version number is " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETLANGUAGE"
##

@NODE getlanguage "GETLANGUAGE"
GETLANGUAGE command:

Obtain the current language that Scion Genealogist is using

	SYNTAX:	GETLANGUAGE

	result: language being used (e.g. "english.language",
	        "deutsch.language")

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	GETLANGUAGE		/* Get current language */
	Say "Current language is " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETFUNKEY"
##

@NODE getfunkey "GETFUNKEY"
GETFUNKEY command:			(Modified return values for V5)

Obtain the string currently assigned to a function key.

	SYNTAX:	GETFUNKEY FunctionKey

	where: 'FunctionKey' is a number from 1 to 40 inclusive, representing
	       the plain and "qualified" function keys F1 - F10.

               Function key numbers: 1 -  10, F1 - F10
                                     11 - 20, Shift F1 - Shift F10
                                     21 - 30, Alt F1 - Alt F10
                                     31 - 40, Ctrl F1 - Ctrl F10

               Note: Numbers greater than 10 were introduced with Scion
	             version 5.

	result: The string currently assigned to a function key.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	GETFUNKEY 3		/* Get string assigned to F3 */
	Say "F3 is currently " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTFUNKEY"
##

@NODE putfunkey "PUTFUNKEY"
PUTFUNKEY command:		(Additional arguments values for V5)

Assign a string to a function key.

	SYNTAX:	PUTFUNKEY FunctionKey "mystring"

	where: 'FunctionKey' is a number from 1 to 40 inclusive, representing
	       the plain and "qualified" function keys F1 - F10.

               Function key numbers: 1 -  10, F1 - F10
                                     11 - 20, Shift F1 - Shift F10
                                     21 - 30, Alt F1 - Alt F10
                                     31 - 40, Ctrl F1 - Ctrl F10

               Note: Numbers greater than 10 were introduced with Scion
	             version 5.

	 and:  "mystring" is a string to assign to that function key.

	result: 0 (FALSE) for error, 1 (TRUE) for success (record updated)

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	PUTFUNKEY 3 "rx Scion2GEDCOM"	/* Set string assigned to F3 */
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETEDITOR"
##

@NODE geteditor "GETEDITOR"
GETEDITOR command:

Obtain the full path/filename of the user-defined text editor. If the
editor is undefined, returns an "empty" string.

	SYNTAX:	GETEDITOR

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	GETEDITOR
	if (RESULT = "") then say "No editor defined"
	else say "Editor path/name = " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETVIEWER"
##

@NODE getviewer "GETVIEWER"
This command is obsolete (but is still supported for backward
compatibility).

Use the new command @{" GETPIXVIEWER " LINK getpixviewer} instead.
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETPIXVIEWER"
##

@NODE getpixviewer "GETPIXVIEWER"
GETPIXVIEWER command:				(V5)

Obtain the full path/filename of the user-defined picture viewer.
If the viewer is undefined, returns an "empty" string.

	SYNTAX:	GETPIXVIEWER

EXAMPLE USAGE:
