	where: 'irn' is the record number to obtain the telephone
	       number of.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	GETPERSPHONE 42
	say "Person 42's phone number = " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTPERSADDR"
##

@NODE putpersaddr "PUTPERSADDR"
PUTPERSADDR command:			(V5)

Set the address of the specified person.

	Syntax: PUTPERSADDR irn "address string"

	where: 'irn' is the record number of the specified person

	       "address string" is the address of the specified person

	NOTE: The address string is a "multi-line" string. To separate
	      each line of the name and address, use the '$' character.

	      For example, to set the address -

		  123 Any Street
		  Sometown
		  NEW ZEALND

	      then enter this as -
	          "123 Any Street$Sometown$NEW ZEALND"

	Do not use more than 4 "lines" as Scion is unable to display more.

	result: 0 (FALSE) for error, 1 (TRUE) for success (record updated)

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyIRN = 5		/* Set MyIRN to person 5 */
	PUTPERSADDR MyIRN "123 Any Street$Sometown$NEW ZEALND"

	See also @{" GETBRKCHAR " LINK getbrkchar} and @{" PUTBRKCHAR " LINK putbrkchar}
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTPERSPHONE"
##

@NODE putpersphone "PUTPERSPHONE"
PUTPERSPHONE command:			(V5)

Set the phone number of the specified person.

	Syntax: PUTPERSPHONE irn "phone number"

	where: 'irn' is the record number of the specified person

	       "phone number" is the telephone number of the specified
	       person

	result: 0 (FALSE) for error, 1 (TRUE) for success (record updated)

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyIRN = 5		/* Set MyIRN to person 5 */
	PUTPERSPHONE MyIRN "+1 +555 123-4567"
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTPERSNOTE"
##

@NODE putpersnote "PUTPERSNOTE"
PUTPERSNOTE command:			(V5)

Set the "attached" note file of the specified person.

	Syntax: PUTPERSNOTE irn "note-filename"

	where: 'irn' is the record number of the specified person

	       "note-filename" is the full path/filename of the notes
	       file to attach to the specified person

	result: 0 (FALSE) for error, 1 (TRUE) for success (record updated)

        NOTE: This function does NOT check if the file actually exists or
	      if the filename is valid.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	MyIRN = 5		/* Set MyIRN to person 5 */
	NoteFile = "WORK:MyFamily/JohnSmith.Note"
	PUTPERSNOTE MyIRN NoteFile
@ENDNODE

