##
## "GETFAMADDR"
##

@NODE getfamaddr "GETFAMADDR"
GETFAMADDR command:			(V5)

Obtain the address for the specified family.

	Syntax: GETFAMADDR fgrn

	where: 'fgrn' is the record number to obtain the address of.

	Note that the address returned is "multi-line" with each line
	separated by a '$' character. Each line of the address can be
	extracted using the ARexx "PARSE VAR" command.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	GETFAMADDR 42
	pers_addr = RESULT
	PARSE VAR pers_addr line_1 '$' line_2 '$' line_3 '$'
	say "First line of family 42's address:" line_1

	See also @{" GETBRKCHAR " LINK getbrkchar} and @{" PUTBRKCHAR " LINK putbrkchar}
@ENDNODE

