##
## "GETMETAPHONE"
##

@NODE getmetaphone "GETMETAPHONE"
GETMETAPHONE command:			(V5)

Obtain the metaphone code for the supplied name.

	Syntax: GETMETAPHONE "name"

	where: "name" is the name to find the metaphone of

	Result is the metaphone for the name, or an empty result string
	for error.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	GETMETAPHONE "Smith"
	if (RESULT = "") then say "Error occured"
	else say "Metaphone for 'Smith' = " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "GETSOUNDEX"
##

@NODE getsoundex "GETSOUNDEX"
GETSOUNDEX command:			(V5)

Obtain the Russell Soundex code for the supplied name.

NOTE: This function will only work for English names. It will NOT work
      with names containing accented characters. If a character that is
      NOT within the ranges 'a' - 'z' and 'A' - 'Z' is encountered,
      this function will return an error (empty result string).

	Syntax: GETSOUNDEX "name"

	where: "name" is the name to find the Sounde code of

	Result is the Soundex code for the name, or an empty result
	string for error.

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	GETSOUNDEX "Smith"
	if (RESULT = "") then say "Error occured"
	else say "Soundex code for 'Smith' = " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "PUTNUMFAMILY"
##

@NODE putnumfamily "PUTNUMFAMILY"
PUTNUMFAMILY command:			(V5)

Creates a NEW specified family and adds it to the specified person
(principal) as a new "marriage"

	Syntax: PUTNUMFAMILY irn fgrn

	where: 'irn' is the Principal to which to add the specified
	       new family

	       'fgrn' is the FGRN of the new family to add to the Principal

	result: On success, returns the new family record number requested,
	        else returns 0 (maybe the specified family was already
		in the database or the person didn't exist). Note that
		asking for person 0 or family 0 will also return 0, but
		this is ALSO a failure.

This command adds a NEW specified family to the specified principal
(as opposed to @{" PUTNEWFAMILY " LINK putnewfamily} which adds the next available family
to the Principal).

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	principal = 5		/* Record number of principal */
	newfamily = 42		/* Number of new family to add to database */
	PUTNUMFAMILY principal newfamily
	If RESULT ~= newfamily then say "Command failed"
	else say "New family was added successfully to " principal

@ENDNODE

##
## "GETFULLNAME"
##

@NODE getfullname "GETFULLNAME"
GETFULLNAME command:			(V5)

Obtain the full name of the specified person.

	Syntax: GETFULLNAME irn format

	where: 'irn' is the record number of the person of interest

	       'format' is the style of the returned full name

	        Possible values of 'format" -

			0 = Default format - without IRN and first name
			    preceeds last name. Eg. "Albert Henry SMITH"

			1 = Include IRN. Eg. "Albert Henry SMITH [42]"

			2 = Last name preceeds first name.
			    Eg. "SMITH, Albert Henry"

			3 = 1+2 (see above).
			    Eg. "SMITH, Albert Henry [42]"

		If 'format' is omitted, returns the "default" form (0).

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	GETFULLNAME 42 3
	say "Full name of person 42 in '3' format is " RESULT
@ENDNODE

##
## "DISSOLVEFAMILY"
##

@NODE dissolvefamily "DISSOLVEFAMILY"
DISSOLVEFAMILY command:			(V5)

Deletes the record of the specified family.

	Syntax: DISSOLVEFAMILY fgrn

	where: 'fgrn' is the record number of the family to delete

	No return value.

	NOTE: ALL references to this family are deleted. For example,
	the children of the family are made into "orphans".

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	DISSOLVEFAMILY 42	/* Delete family group 42 */
@ENDNODE

##
## "REMOVECHILD"
##

@NODE removechild "REMOVECHILD"
REMOVECHILD command:			(V5)

Removes specified child from specified family

	Syntax: REMOVECHILD fgrn irn

	where: 'fgrn' is the family group to remove the specified
	       child from

	       'irn' is the record number of the child to remove from
	       the specified family

	For example, "REMOVECHILD 42 11" will remove the child with
	IRN = 11 from the family with FGRN = 42.

	No return value.

	NOTE: The child's personal record is not affected, but the child
	      is made into an "orphan".

EXAMPLE USAGE:
	MyPort = "SCIONGEN"	/* Point at Scion Genealogist port */
	Address value MyPort	/* Change ARexx address to that port */
	family = 42		/* Family to remove child from */
	childirn = 11		/* Child's record number */
	REMOVECHILD family childirn
@ENDNODE
